   My being bristled at the touch<br>
Hair whipped about my face<br>
   My garments danced beneath my clutch<br>
<br>
I turned to face the breeze<br>
   A soft caress it then became<br>
A gentle smile replaced the scowl<br>
   And ember soon was flame<br>
<br>
The breeze was constant<br>
   Carrying the sweetest song<br>
Although it could not be shared<br>
   I hoped it lasted long<br>
<br>
One day the breeze was stilled<br>
   Clouds moved in with rain<br>
My garments drenched in sadness<br>
   My heart was wrought in pain<br>
<br>
Stillness for so many nights<br>
   Cold and black despair<br>
The call to sleep seemed only right<br>
   Yet I could not venture there<br>
<br>
One day my ears a rustle heard<br>
   A breeze anew?  How could it be?<br>
Yet swirling madly all about<br>
   I let my hair fall free<br>
<br>
The laughter floats atop the breeze<br>
   Life flourishes imbued<br>
With gentle joys each day revealed<br>
   And love is found renewed <p>Jezeran Hateslayer<BR>
